+## GitHub Backup Behavior
+
+The first GitHub connector writes a redacted package into a local knowledge-bank checkout. It does not push by default.
+
+| Option | Behavior |
+|---|---|
+| no flag | Write package locally |
+| `--commit` | Commit package in knowledge-bank repo |
+| `--push` | Commit and push package |
+
 ## Design Rule
 
 If a connector is fragile, keep it optional. The core should still work through manual capture and file import.
